  18 Sep 2004; Sven Wegener <swegener@gentoo.org>
  silc-toolkit-0.9.12-r3.ebuild:
  Changed order of sed scripts to avoid running automake at compile time. Closes
  bug 64495.

  17 Sep 2004; Andrej Kacian <ticho@gentoo.org> silc-toolkit-0.9.12-r3.ebuild:
  Modify install location of tutorial files also in Makefile.am, since on some
  systems (amd64 reported this so far), the build process seems to start over
  and recreate Makefile .in from .am. Thanks to Jocelyn Mayer
  <l_indien@magic.fr> for the report and following fix (bug #63089).

*silc-toolkit-0.9.12-r3 (05 Sep 2004)

  05 Sep 2004; Andrej Kacian <ticho@gentoo.org> silc-toolkit-0.9.12-r3.ebuild:
  Fixed install locations.

  05 Sep 2004; Andrej Kacian <ticho@gentoo.org> :
  Install /usr/lib/pkgconfig/silc.pc, as some packages will need it soon. Next
  official release of silc-toolkit should install this file itself, so the
  ebuild will have to be adjusted. Closes #62843. Also, use $(get_libdir).

